vocal cords white and glistening.context: Inspection of the vocal cords underneath the microscope revealed them to be white and glistening without any mucosal abnormalities.

right vocal cord slightly more hyperemic.context: It should be mentioned that the right vocal cord did appear to be slightly more hyperemic, however, there were no mucosal abnormalities identified.

papillomatous type growth.context: Inspection of the vallecula revealed a fullness on the right side with a papillomatous type growth that appeared very friable.

studding along the right lateral wall.context: Again in the right piriform sinus, there was noted to be studding along the right lateral wall of the piriform sinus.
